Tom - I&#39;m not sure, but if I were to guess, I would guess that Python 
is not finding the temporary Python script Cantera generates to process 
CTI input files.  Judging from the pathname that appears in the error 
message &quot;C:&#92;DOCUME~1&#92;tps&#92;LOCALS~1&#92;Temp/&quot; it looks like you are running 
the demos from a directory with a long name, probably containing 
spaces.  Try copying the demos to a directory with a name that 
Windows/DOS does not mangle, or at least not as badly (short with no 
spaces). If that doesn&#39;t work, try running the temporary Python script 
manually, and look for error messages - for example, type at a command 
prompt:

python .check1100822275.pyw

Hope this helps.

Dave



